Level 1 - Core Joins
1. List all students with their course names and teacher names.
(Only students with valid courses & teachers)

2. Display all students and their courses.
Include students who have not enrolled in any course.

3. Show all courses along with assigned teachers.
Include courses without teachers.

Level 2 - Filtering + Logic
4. Find students enrolled after 2022 along with their course & teacher.

5. List all courses that currently have NO students enrolled.

6. Show each teacher and the number of courses they teach.
Include teachers teaching zero courses.

Level 3 - CROSS JOIN & Analysis
7. Generate all possible student–course combinations.
(Display student name and course name)
Use CROSS JOIN

Level 4 - SELF JOIN (Very Important)
8. Display employees and their managers’ names.
Include top-level employees with no manager.

9. Find employees who report directly to the CEO.

Level 5 - Think Like an Analyst
10. Find students whose course does not have a teacher assigned.


------------------------------------------------------------

Level 1 - Core JOIN Practice
1. List all students with their course name and teacher name.
2. Display all students, even those not enrolled in any course, along with course name.
3. Show course name, teacher name, and number of students enrolled in each course.
4. Find all students taught by “Ms. Verma”.
Level 2 - Thinking in Relationships
5. List courses that currently have no students enrolled.
6. Show students enrolled in courses that run longer than 6 weeks.
7. Find teachers who are teaching more than one course.
Level 3 - Advanced JOIN Logic
8. Generate all possible student-course combinations (regardless of enrollment).
9. Display students enrolled in Data Science department courses only.
10. (Self-Join Style Thinking - Prep for Hierarchies)
Assume students can mentor other students
(add column mentor_id referencing student_id)
Write a query to show:
student name
mentor name
(Conceptual self-join — even if you do not run it)